race.comment: Loads of pressure up front which will suit BLACK ORA (6). Got back but stormed home to score last time when fresh from a spell and looks hard to hold out again. LORD SHIVA (7) resumes and boasts a great fresh record, including when resuming last campaign. Fitter for a trial and will take catching. JAZ SESSION (5) is another resuming and goes well fresh. Course and distance suits and O'Donnell has a great record while aboard. Serious threat. SUNLIT FRESCO (10) was many lengths off best last time and vetted. Previous run augers well for this and with the light weight and low draw is worth another try.  EJAZ (2) is the most interesting runner of the day. Former Singapore galloper who resumes for new yard as a gelding. Goes well fresh, fitter for two trials and aided by the claim. Big watch.
